STEP 1: Install Node.js

Go to nodejs.org

Download LTS (Recommended)

Install it
(Node includes npm automatically)



---

STEP 2: Open Your Terminal

Use any of these:

Command Prompt (Windows)

PowerShell

Terminal (Mac / Linux)



---

STEP 3: Check if Node & npm are installed

Type:

node -v
npm -v

If you get version numbers → you’re ready.


---

STEP 4: Create Your Project Folder

mkdir myproject
cd myproject


---

STEP 5: Initialize npm (Create package.json)

npm init -y


---

STEP 6: Install a Package

Type:

npm install express

(You can install any package, not only express)

This creates:

node_modules folder

Adds dependency inside package.json



---

STEP 7: Install Developer Tools (Optional)

For testing, linting, etc.

npm install --save-dev nodemon


---

STEP 8: Install All Dependencies (When starting a project you cloned)

If someone gave you a project:

npm install

This reads package.json and installs everything.


---

STEP 9: Run Your App (Example)

If your file is app.js:

node app.js


---

STEP 10: Uninstall a Package

npm uninstall express
